# 1) Legacy /330 short-URL alias for the $330 audit offer — 308 to canonical /micro-offer.
#    /330 → /micro-offer.
#    Both with and without trailing slash so any external / short-URL link lands on canonical.
#    CF Pages uses :splat on the destination side to substitute the wildcard segment.
#    (Removed the trailing-slash row from the SPA-fallback line; we use a Router-side hook
#     to strip trailing slashes before Wouter matches, see client/src/hooks/useStrippedLocation.ts
#     and the hook prop on <Router> in App.tsx.)
/330            /micro-offer            308
/330/           /micro-offer/           308
/330/*          /micro-offer/:splat     308

# 1b) Self-contained owner login — bypasses the SPA bundle and the service worker
#     so a stale SW or browser extension can't break the auth flow.
/owner-login         /owner-login.html        301

# 1c) Catch-all proxy /v1/* → /api/v1-proxy/* so the SPA bundle can talk
#     same-origin to admin APIs and avoid cross-origin blocks. The Pages Function
#     at functions/api/v1-proxy/[[path]].js forwards to the real Worker.
/v1/*               /api/v1-proxy/:splat      200

# 2) Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback: preserve clean direct routes for Wouter client routing.
#    The Router hook (useStrippedLocation) handles trailing slashes before matching.
#    DO NOT remove this line — without it direct loads of /portfolio/:id etc fail.
/*    /index.html   200

# 2b) Hosted quote pages (/q/<slug>) — must be served as SPA so wouter can render
#     the dynamic slug. The catch-all above is processed but the static
#     middleware can still short-circuit on dynamic paths. Explicit mirror rule.
/q/*    /index.html   200
